{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17503767","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17503767"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:07:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:07:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2077"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2077","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2077"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.03,0.3,0.57,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2077"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82003"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2077","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2077"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2077"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67257"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"165"},{"type":"tags","id":"2255"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"130"},{"type":"contributions","id":"131"},{"type":"contributions","id":"168"},{"type":"contributions","id":"184"},{"type":"contributions","id":"28683"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40413"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42456"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43115"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82003","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/82003"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 58-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a 12-month history of chronic cough. He reports worsening fatigue, weakness, and haemoptysis over the past two weeks. He has a medical history of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease and was admitted to hospital three months ago for an exacerbation requiring two weeks of oral prednisolone. His only regular medication is tiotropium inhaler. He has a 30 pack-year smoking history and drinks 5-10 standard drinks of alcohol per week.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears unwell. His pulse rate is 88/min, blood pressure 156/88 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 95% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. He has thin skin with multiple bruises over the arms and legs, and generalised hyperpigmentation. A random capillary glucose reading is 11.8 mmol/L.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely underlying cause for this man\u0027s clinical features?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Adrenal hyperplasia","Alcohol abuse","Exogenous steroid use","Ectopic ACTH production","Pituitary adenoma"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with features of Cushing\u0027s syndrome in the context of likely underlying lung malignancy. The combination of chronic cough, haemoptysis, and significant smoking history suggests small cell lung cancer, which commonly causes \u003Cstrong\u003Eectopic ACTH production\u003C/strong\u003E due to its neuroendocrine origin. The clinical features of Cushing\u0027s syndrome include thin skin, easy bruising, hyperpigmentation, hypertension, and diabetes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdrenal hyperplasia\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents in early life with features of adrenal insufficiency, or in young adults with virilisation, acne, testicular masses, or infertility. It would be an unusual cause of Cushing\u0027s syndrome in this age group.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlcohol abuse\u003C/strong\u003E can produce pseudo-Cushingoid features, but this patient\u0027s alcohol consumption is within recommended limits and would not account for the severity of his presentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExogenous steroid use\u003C/strong\u003E is the most common cause of Cushing\u0027s syndrome overall. However, this patient\u0027s brief course of prednisolone three months ago would not explain his current clinical features.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPituitary adenoma\u003C/strong\u003E (Cushing\u0027s disease) is an important cause of endogenous Cushing\u0027s syndrome. However, the absence of headache or visual symptoms, combined with the presence of haemoptysis in a heavy smoker, makes this diagnosis less likely than ectopic ACTH production.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Small cell lung cancers commonly produce ectopic ACTH causing Cushing\u0027s syndrome due to their neuroendocrine origin","The combination of Cushing\u0027s features and haemoptysis in a smoker should raise suspicion for underlying malignancy","Clinical features of Cushing\u0027s syndrome include thin skin, easy bruising, hyperpigmentation, hypertension and diabetes"],"references":["Soomro Z, Youssef M, Yust-Katz S, Jalali A, Patel AJ, Mandel J. Paraneoplastic syndromes in small cell lung cancer. J Thorac Dis. 2020;12(10):6253-6263. doi:10.21037/jtd.2020.03.88","Anwar A, Jafri F, Ashraf S, Jafri MAS, Fanucchi M. Paraneoplastic syndromes in lung cancer and their management. Ann Transl Med. 2019;7(15):359. doi:10.21037/atm.2019.04.86"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67257"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2077"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67257","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/67257"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-27T18:09:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-27T